The government will provide health insurance and a contribution to pension funds to all artists who will be crown winners in the Tanzania Music Awards (TMA 2021). Minister of Culture, Arts and Sports, Mohamed Mchengerwa said on Saturday, that the package will benefit the winner and their families for a period of one year. Winners will also receive a special allowance during the award night. The Minister also instructed that all the names of the artists who took part in the award ceremony must be listed on the ministryâ€™s special board. Permanent Secretary Ministry of Culture, Arts and Sports Dr. Hassan Abbas is already in talks with insurance institutions in the country to link artists with the service across the country. The awards are being held for the first time in Dar es Salaam after seven years.